Using the Amatrix Management Studio

 


The Amatrix Management Studio Allows You To Manage Your Business.

 

 

·         Logistics Management

·         Project Management

·         Human Resources

1.        HR

2.        Payrolls

3.        Outsourcing

4.        Recruitment and Selection

·         Customer Management

·         Product Management

·         Task Management

 

 

Remember, Before Navigating or Searching Save Your Data Unless You Selected Yes in the Use Dynamic Summary/Saving in the Database Menu

 

 

Topic 1 [Logistics Management]

 

 

To Start Of, You Must Create A New Logistics Data Entry Element By Clicking on the  Button, in The Interface as Shown Below inside the Red Circle

 

 

                                  

                                                                                                                         

                                   

Now a New Logistical ID Batch Shall Be Created

 

 

 

 

And Your Data Entry Counter will Change from 0 to 1,2,3 this Number represents the Count of Your Logistical Entries.

 

 

 

 

Now You may Add All The Specified Data for Your Logistics, Remember That You May Choose Your Logistical Staff From Human Resource Management; in the Staff Text Box Just Click on the Row of the Employee You want To Add

 

 

 

 

Now You May Be Wondering What the Below Shown Space is used For

 

 

 

This Window is To Select Stock items of Selected Products from Product Management that You Would Like to Deliver or, Would Like Delivered. Click on Create new Undelivered Product then, Click on Choose Product to Choose an Inventory Item of a Selected Product Range

 

 

Topic 2 [Project Management]

 

 

Project Management Is a Data Entry System for Projects Occurring Within Your Business.

 

 

 

 

Add new Rows By Writing in Empty Cells, in an Empty Row as Shown Below

 

 

 

 

You May View Specified Records Which Satisfy Extreme Specifications by Going to the Data Commands Menu and then to the Show Where Menu after Which Choose a Column Name Coincidental to the Main Data View and Select an Operation as Equal To Enter The Data You Want To See and Click on Ok

 

 

 

 

You May Also See Time Spans of Your Projects First Remember to Insert Dates For Your Projects

 

 

 

 

Now Click on Generate Time Line button and it Will Draw a Graphical Representation of the When and Time of Every Prject Within the Specified Year You Chose it will Take Your Project to Finish categorized in a normal 12 month year as shown below [Remember to Save Your Data Before Generating a Timeline To Make Sure Your TimeLine Will Be Displayed also With Your New Data]

 

 

 

 

Topic 3 [Human Resources Management]

 

 

HR Management Helps You Take Care of Your Human Resources, Payrolls and Future Employees including Your Outsourced Employees. To Start Of, You Must Create A New Logistics Data Entry Element By Clicking on the  Button in The Interface as Shown Below, inside the Red Circle

 

 

 

 

Now You May Enter all The Data You Would Need To About Your Employees

 

 

                Sub-Topic [Payrolls]

 

 

To Start Of, The Employee Editor and the Payroll Editor are Inter-Connected, So Choose the Employee of Which you Would Like to Edit the Payroll.

 

Now the Only Area You Will need Help With is the Payed On Tab/Area. Click on the  button and Enter Your Details, Remember to Save Your Values by Pressing the Save Button in the Same Tool Bar on top of the Data Field and, Remember that You Wont Have To Put The Payment Amount Here It is Assumed That the Payment Amount is the One You Inputted in the General Payment Information Tab/Area

 

 

 

Remember, that The Payed On Area is only For Denoting When You Have Payed an Employee and Keeping Track of So

 

 

                Sub-Topic [Outsourced Employees]

 

 

You may Enter Details For Employees Entered in the Employees Editor as Outsourced Employees. To Do So Create an Out Sourced Office in the Field Shown Below inside the Out-Sourcing Tab

 

 

 

 

Now Go to The Employees Tab and Click on the Show All Button to Show All Your Employees again, as Outsourcing Changes the View to Show You Details of the Office Row You Have Selected in the Out-Sourcing Tab. Now Go Down to the Outsourcing Area in the Employee Editor

 

 

 

 

Choose Yes for the Is Out-Sourced Choose Box and, Choose an Office from the Out-Sourced to Office box (These Will be Loaded From the Out-Sourcing Tab), Now You may Go Back to the Out-Sourcing Tab and choose the Office You Choose for that Employee, There-after You Will See the Employee in the Outsourced Employees Section

 

 

 

 

                Sub-Topic [Recruitment and Selection]

 

 

This Tab Allows You To Keep Track of Your Potential Employees and the Current Selection Process. All Employees Entered Here are not In Relation to Those in the Employee Editor, yet Have a Ranking Function to Help You Through the Three Final Phases of Recruitment

 

 

 

 

Remember to Add a Rank to Your Employees to Denote Who is in the First, Second or Third and Final Stage or Recruitment

 

 

 

 

(Continued From Above) So You May Search or choose to View Certain Records with a Certain Rank

 

 

 



Remember to Save Before Searching or Selecting the Above Ranks if Youve Entered any New Data

 

 

 

Topic 4 [Customer Management]

 

 

Customer Management is a PR Solution That Helps You Keep Track of Clients and the Products They Purchased, This Application is also Interwoven to the Front Desk Mode just as the Product Management Application is, Start of by Clicking on the  button to Create a new Customer

 

 

 

 

You Will need Help with One Part of this Application: the Purchase Information Area/Tab

 

 

 

 

Remember You Must Have Products Created in the Product Management Application, Now Click on the Product Purchased Choose Box (do Not click on the Arrow), Now a Menu will Appear as Below

 

 

 

 

Select a Product (in this Case Product, 59830958), and the Other Data Box Will Appear with Your Inventory Items of the Product Range You Have Chosen

 

 

 

 

You May Pick One Product at a Time, Now Click on Ok

 

 

 

 

Now The above Will Appear, Click on Add Product, Press X to Remove a product From the Purchase Information

 

 

Topic 5 [Product Management]

 

 

To Start Of, You Must Create A New Product Data Entry Element By Clicking on the  Button in The Interface as Shown Below

 

 

 

 

Now You May add All the Data You May Need to, But Here are Some things You may Struggle With. Lets Start Of With Your Inventory Information. Remember, that Basic information Consists of the General Information Regarding a Type of Product, such as Pantene Shampoo but, You Will Need to List Your Inventory of Pantene Shampoos

 

 

 

 

Add the Reference Number of Your Product (not the Bar-Code We will Show You how to Set That Later on though), If you Dont know What a Reference Number is Write the Barcode of Your Product in the Add Bulk inventory Item Text Box

 

 

 

 

Now, Choose When You Bought or Manufactured the Specified Item

 

 

 

 

After Which, Click on the Add Product Item Button To add This Inventory Item to Your Actual Inventory Data, Now You May Edit Various Parameters, Remember that this Information is Interwoven into the Front Desk Mode of Amatrix so To Show You When You Sold Certain Inventory And To Which Customer (Which You May See in Customer Management)

 

You May add Your Barcode Information in the Below Shown Field in the Inventory Information Inventory Item You Have Chosen

 

 

 

 

You May Add Stock Information, Yet this Information is Usually Optional for Most Businesses, its a good Way of Tracking Your Stock Purchases, Click on the  Button in the Area Shown Below to Get Started

 

 

 

 

 

Topic 6 [Task Management]

 

 

 

Task Management Helps You Coordinate Tasks With Your Staff Start off By Searching For The Staff Member of Press the  Button in the Area Shown Below to Create an New Task

 

 

 

 

Remember You Can Choose What Staff You Want To add in A New Row By Selecting One from Human Resources Management by Clicking on the Add Staff For Current Row Button as Shown Below
